                <pb facs="0488" n="476" xml:id="pg_476"/>
                <p rend="center">1. <hi rend="smallcaps">Austria: Ration Scales</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council invited the Governments of the United Kingdom, United States,
                    U.S.S.R. and France to despatch telegrams to their representatives on the Allied
                    Council for Austria in the terms of the draft set out in C.F.M.(45) 82.<note
                        n="17" xml:id="d170fn17">For text of telegram regarding food ration scale,
                        see second message quoted in telegram 10181, Delsec 86, October 1, 3 p.m.,
                        from London, <ref target="frus1945v03#pg_620">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps"
                                >iii</hi>, p. 620</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">2. <hi rend="smallcaps">Restitution</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council invited the Deputies to continue their consideration of the question
                    of Restitution on the basis of the French memorandum (C.F.M.(45) 38<note n="18"
                        xml:id="d170fn18">September 20, <ref target="#pg_285">p.
                    285</ref>.</note>).</p>
                <p rend="center">3. <hi rend="smallcaps">Preparation of Final Protocol</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council instructed the Protocol Committee to prepare drafts of four Protocols
                    on the lines proposed by M. Molotov, taking as a basis the Russian text prepared
                    by the Soviet Delegation.</p>
                <p rend="center">4. <hi rend="smallcaps">Preparation of Final Communiqué</hi>
                </p>
                <p>An exchange of views took place. The Council agreed to meet again at 9:30 p.m.
                    that evening in order to consider (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) questions arising
                    on the final Protocol and Communiqué, and (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) the
                    proposal of the Soviet Delegation regarding the future procedure for the
                    preparation of Peace Treaties.</p>
